<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-255-559  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 255 559.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  Jan 9 1989 n295 p47(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>VAR exits health care; McDonnell Douglas unit revamps computergroup. (Value-Added Reseller)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Lucas, Peter.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>McDonnell Douglas Information Systems Co, a VAR, is in the processof reorganizing.andP;  As a consequence, the firm is shedding thoseoperations which are unrelated to the aerospace industry.andP;  Thecompany has already sold off Vitek Inc, one of two health careunits that it operated, while another remains on the market.andP;  Thecompany's vertical market endeavors will be redirected into salesand service for networks, high-end computer platforms, large-scaleintegration and application software development.andP;  The divisionwill continue to build hardware for other McDonnell Douglasoperations and will seek agreements with other VARs in certainselected vertical markets.andP;  The firm laid off 200 direct salesrepresentatives as a result of the reorganization.andP;  Much of thestaff was hired by the software companies that previously hadworked with McDonnell Douglas on joint-marketing agreements.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   McDonnell Douglas Information Systems Group (divestment)VITEK Inc. (acquisitions and mergers).andO;Topic:     Value-Added ResellersHealth CareDivestmentLayoffReorganizationBusiness Planning.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>